{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04316/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04316"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:43:16"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["plan américain"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, pan, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman laughs as she undresses in a dressing room."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04316","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04316"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/canvas/1/357f96b2-2e5f-4ea3-9484-b14511b31216","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:43:05.384Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The playfulness and flirtatiousness exhibited by Alma in this scene is part of Vicky Krieps’s character development. As she puts it, she viewed their relationship “not as a duel but as a duet – a dance...The power levels are different in Alma and Reynolds. Paul left this very open. Many relationships can become difficult and it can be hard to find a way back... Sometimes, if you look at older couples who have been together for years, they have the strangest ways of staying together – they play games, often sexual...She is like an equation you can’t solve – a poem.” The actress turned to \"Emily Dickinson’s poetry as a gloss on the character, a way of reaching ‘beyond what we know’” (Kellaway, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW250242246 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/jan/21/vicky-krieps-daniel-day-lewis-interview-phantom-thread\"><u>Actor Vicky Krieps</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04316/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:708.0484522207269,151.73620457604312,492.27456258411826,547.8331090174966"}}}]}]}]}